arcade.patch.agent.process

Class PatchProcessMetabolismComplex

  • java.lang.Object
    • arcade.patch.agent.process.PatchProcess
      • arcade.patch.agent.process.PatchProcessMetabolism
        • arcade.patch.agent.process.PatchProcessMetabolismComplex
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Process

    public class PatchProcessMetabolismComplex
extends PatchProcessMetabolism
    Extension of PatchProcessMetabolism for complex metabolism.

    PatchProcessMetabolismComplex explicitly includes pyruvate intermediate between glycolysis and oxidative phosphorylation and glucose uptake is based on cell surface area. Metabolic preference between glycolysis and oxidative phosphorylation is controlled by METABOLIC_PREFERENCE. The glycolysis pathway will compensate if there is not enough oxygen to meet energetic requirements through the oxidative phosphorylation pathway given the specified metabolic preference.

    PatchProcessMetabolismComplex will increase cell mass (using specified fractions of internal glucose and pyruvate) if:

    • cell is dividing and less than double in size
    • cell is below critical mass for maintenance

    PatchProcessMetabolismComplex will decrease cell mass if:

    • cell has negative energy indicating insufficient nutrients
    • cell is above critical mass for maintenance

    Internal pyruvate is removed through conversion to lactate.

    • Constructor Detail

      • PatchProcessMetabolismComplex

        public PatchProcessMetabolismComplex(PatchCell cell)
        Creates a complex metabolism Process for the given PatchCell.

        Module has internal glucose and pyruvate.

        Loaded parameters include:

        • METABOLIC_PREFERENCE = preference for glycolysis over oxidative phosphorylation
        • CONVERSION_FRACTION = fraction of internal glucose / pyruvate converted to mass
        • MINIMUM_MASS_FRACTION = minimum viable cell mass fraction
        • RATIO_GLUCOSE_PYRUVATE = preference for glucose over pyruvate for mass
        • LACTATE_RATE = rate of lactate production
        • AUTOPHAGY_RATE = rate of autophagy
        • GLUCOSE_UPTAKE_RATE = rate of glucose uptake
        Parameters:
        cell - the PatchCell the process is associated with
